Enum ControlCharacter

  • java.lang.Object
    • java.lang.Enum<ControlCharacter>
      • com.acrolinx.javasdk.api.extraction.ControlCharacter
  • All Implemented Interfaces:
    Serializable, Comparable<ControlCharacter>

    public enum ControlCharacter
extends Enum<ControlCharacter>
    The ControlCharacters are used to control the server-side tokenization.

    • Enum Constant Summary

      Enum Constants 
      Enum Constant and Description
      DOT_ADDED_BY_CLIENT
      Separates two sentences.
      EMPTY_ELEMENT
      Is used if some text or objects are skipped by extraction.
      SKIPPED_ELEMENT_END
      The whole text from SKIPPED_ELEMENT_START till SKIPPED_ELEMENT_END is ignored.
      SKIPPED_ELEMENT_START
      Notifies that the following text is skipped until SKIPPED_ELEMENT_END is reached.
      SPACE_ADDED_BY_CLIENT
      Separates two words.
